Package frc.robot

Class Lib4150ElapsedTime

java.lang.Object
frc.robot.Lib4150ElapsedTime
public class Lib4150ElapsedTime extends Object
The Lib4150ElapsedTime class calculates the elapsed time from a particular starting point. Generally the execute function is called with the system time. Optionally, the system time can be read from the FPGA clock.

  • Method Details

    • execElapsedTime

      public double execElapsedTime(boolean init)
      Calculate the elapsed time in seconds since init was turned off. If init has never been true then the returned value is the elapsed time since the system was booted.
      Parameters:
      init - - boolean - When TRUE elapsed time is set to zero.
      Returns:
      elapsedTime - double - number of seconds elapsed since init was true - seconds.

    • execElapsedTime

      public double execElapsedTime(boolean init, double systemTime)
      Calculate the elapsed time in seconds since init was turned off. If init has never been true then the returned value is the elapsed time since the system was booted.
      Parameters:
      init - - boolean - When TRUE elapsed time is set to zero.
      systemTime - - double - System elapsed time - seconds.
      Returns:
